This is simple LaTeX equation server (or whatever), used by me for some presentations. It uses external programs:
* LaTeX
* divps
* convert (from ImageMagick)

It needs access to /tmp

Just run server by 'merb -I seksi.rb -n seksi -m /tmp -l fatal -P /dev/null -l /dev/null -e production -p 1111', go to http://127.0.0.1:1111 and type:
\lim_{x\to\infty} \frac{x^2+2x}{x^3+2} 

If you want daemonize it add -d flag.
